metadata.title: Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche
aws::graph::propositions: Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche Aircraft Specifications
The Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche has two rearmost seats occupying the baggage compartment.
The rearmost seats in the Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche are quite small.
The Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche is a four-seat twin-engined cabin aircraft.
The Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche is powered by two 160 hp (119 kW) Lycoming IO-320-B1A engines.
The Lycoming IO-320-B1A engines are mounted in wing-mounted nacelles.
The Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche was available in five levels of equipment fit.
The Standard level is one equipment fit option for the Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche.
The Custom level includes additional instruments.
The Executive level includes additional instruments and radio equipment.
The Sportsman level includes Palm Beach interior and exterior.
The Sportsman level includes AltiMaticII autopilot.
The Professional level includes full IFR panel.
The Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche B has a third cabin window on each side.
The Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche B has an optional fifth seat.
The Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche B has an optional sixth seat.
The Piper PA-30 Turbo Twin Comanche is a turbonormalized version of the PA-30B Twin Comanche.
The Piper PA-30 Turbo Twin Comanche is powered by two Rajay turbonormalized IO-320-C1A piston engines.
The Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche C has a new instrument panel compared to previous models.
The Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche C has new switches compared to previous models.
The Piper PA-30 Twin Comanche C has other minor variations compared to previous models.

text:
The two rearmost seats, occupying the baggage compartment, are quite small.

PA-30 Twin Comanche
Four-seat twin-engined cabin aircraft powered by two 160 hp (119 kW) Lycoming IO-320-B1A engines in wing-mounted nacelles. The aircraft was available in five levels of equipment fit:
Standard.
Custom  additional instruments
Executive  additional instruments and radio equipment
Sportsman  Palm Beach interior and exterior and AltiMaticII autopilot
Professional  full IFR panel
PA-30 Twin Comanche B
PA-30 with a third cabin window on each side and an optional fifth or sixth seat
PA-30 Turbo Twin Comanche
Turbonormalized version of the PA-30B Twin Comanche, powered by two Rajay turbonormalized IO-320-C1A piston engines
PA-30 Twin Comanche C
Twin Comanche B with new instrument panel, switches, and other minor variations.
